 #[command(hide = true)]\n    PostCommitRetry {\n        commit: String,\n        repo: String,\n        timestamp: i64,\n    },\n}\n```\n\nAdd dispatch in `main()`.\n\n#### B. Add `spawn_background_retry` helper (`src/main.rs`)\n\nAfter writing a pending record (3 places: line 312, 351, 360), spawn the background process:\n\n```rust\nfn spawn_background_retry(commit: &str, repo: &str, timestamp: i64) {\n    let exe = match std::env::current_exe() {\n        Ok(e) => e,\n        Err(_) => return,\n    };\n    let _ = Command::new(&exe)\n        .args([\"hook\", \"post-commit-retry\", commit, repo, &timestamp.to_string()])\n        .stdin(Stdio::null())\n        .stdout(Stdio::null())\n        .stderr(Stdio::null())\n        .spawn();\n}\n```\n\nUses `spawn()` (non-blocking) — parent returns immediately, child is reparented to init/launchd when parent exits. No `setsid` needed (child has no terminal association since stdio is null).\n\nstderr is `Stdio::null()` — background retry output is intentionally silent. The note's existence is the proof it worked. Any `eprintln!` calls in shared helpers go to `/dev/null` for the background path, to stderr for the synchronous path — no special handling needed.\n\n#### C. Implement `run_hook_post_commit_retry` (`src/main.rs`)\n\nBackoff schedule: sleep 1s, 2s, 4s, 8s, 16s, 32s (6 retries, ~63s total).\n\nEach iteration:\n1. Sleep\n2. Check `note_exists_at` — if note already attached, clean up pending and exit\n3. Collect candidate files (using same ±600s window as hook — the mtime hasn't changed, it's the *content* that's changed)\n4. Scan for commit hash\n5. If found & verified: format note, attach, remove pending, optionally push\n6. If not found: continue to next backoff step\n\nOn exhaustion: exit silently — pending system handles long-term retry.\n\n#### D. Extract `try_resolve_single_commit` helper (`src/main.rs`)\n\nRefactor the resolution logic (currently duplicated between `hook_post_commit_inner` and `retry_pending_for_repo`) into a shared helper that both the existing retry and the new background retry can call.\n\n### Files to modify\n\n- `src/main.rs` — all changes (enum, dispatch, spawn helper, retry function, refactored helper, dedup cleanup)\n\n### No new dependencies needed\n\n- `std::process::Command::spawn()` for detaching\n- `std::thread::sleep` for backoff delays\n- All git `_at` variants already exist in `src/git.rs`\n\n## Verification\n\n1. `cargo fmt && cargo clippy` — no warnings\n2. `cargo test` — all existing tests pass\n3. Manual test: make a commit in this repo while in a Claude Code session, verify the note gets attached within a few seconds (check with `git notes --ref refs/notes/ai-sessions show HEAD`)\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/daveslutzkin/.claude/projects/-Users-daveslutzkin-dev-ai-barometer/c42e77ff-a87c-455d-bca0-a180c8b3f94b.jsonl"},"uuid":"00831952-947b-409b-9453-e7ad0995f088","timestamp":"2026-02-09T20:04:12.471Z","planContent":"# Plan: Post-commit hook fixes\n\n## Context\n\nThe post-commit hook has two issues:\n\n1. **Stale pending cleanup**: When the hook early-exits because a note already exists (dedup check at line 281), it skips `retry_pending_for_repo` (line 369), so pending files for already-resolved commits never get cleaned up.\n\n2. **Chicken-and-egg timing**: The hook runs before `git commit` returns to the calling agent. The agent only writes the commit hash to its session log *after* the commit returns. So the hook can never find the hash on first run. The current fallback is the pending retry on the *next* commit, which could be hours/days later.\n\n## Fix 1: Clean up pending on dedup early-exit\n\n**File:** `src/main.rs` — `hook_post_commit_inner()` (line 268)\n\nAt the dedup check (line 281-283), before returning, remove any pending record for this commit:\n\n```rust\nif git::note_exists(&hea