{"parentUuid":"f97d7157-ce34-4b96-a76c-5553d0c47534","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/daveslutzkin/dev/ai-barometer","sessionId":"0eae50f1-5fc6-498a-8228-14a4199c9db2","version":"2.1.37","gitBranch":"main","slug":"concurrent-stargazing-gadget","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012insYJ647NS91gNKrcbKc7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→mod agents;\n     2→mod git;\n     3→mod note;\n     4→mod pending;\n     5→mod push;\n     6→mod scanner;\n     7→\n     8→use anyhow::Result;\n     9→use clap::{Parser, Subcommand};\n    10→use std::process;\n    11→\n    12→/// AI Barometer: attach AI coding agent session logs to Git commits via git notes.\n    13→///\n    14→/// Provides provenance and measurement of AI-assisted development\n    15→/// without polluting commit history.\n    16→#[derive(Parser, Debug)]\n    17→#[command(name = \"ai-barometer\", version, about)]\n    18→struct Cli {\n    19→    #[command(subcommand)]\n    20→    command: Command,\n    21→}\n    22→\n    23→#[derive(Subcommand, Debug)]\n    24→enum Command {\n    25→    /// Install AI Barometer: set up git hooks and run initial hydration.\n    26→    Install {\n    27→        /// Optional GitHub org filter for push scoping.\n    28→        #[arg(long)]\n    29→        org: Option<String>,\n    30→    },\n    31→\n    32→    /// Git hook entry points.\n    33→    Hook {\n    34→        #[command(subcommand)]\n    35→        hook_command: HookCommand,\n    36→    },\n    37→\n    38→    /// Backfill AI session notes for recent commits.\n    39→    Hydrate {\n    40→        /// How far back to scan, e.g. \"7d\" for 7 days.\n    41→        #[arg(long, default_value = \"7d\")]\n    42→        since: String,\n    43→\n    44→        /// Push notes to remote after hydration.\n    45→        #[arg(long)]\n    46→        push: bool,\n    47→    },\n    48→\n    49→    /// Retry attaching notes for pending (unresolved) commits.\n    50→    Retry